  <title translate="true">Farm Irrigation Types Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Farm Irrigation Types Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Irrigation Types</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to specify the names and properties of the irrigation types. The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Crop Properties</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Model|Farm Process|Farm Irrigation Types...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For each irrigation type specified, an integer global variable will be created whose name is the name of the irrigation type and whose value is the number of that irrigation type. Those global variables can be used wherever you need to specify an irrigation type.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Besides the names of the irrigation types, the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Irrigation Types</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box can be used to specify </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="LAND_USE-Farm-Process-V4-Land-" anchor="EVAPORATION_IRRIGATION_FRACTION" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">EVAPORATION_IRRIGATION_FRACTION</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="LAND_USE-Farm-Process-V4-Land-" anchor="SURFACEWATER_LOSS_FRACTION_PRECIPITATION" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SURFACEWATER_LOSS_FRACTION_IRRIGATION</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> both of which are part of the LAND_USE block of the FMP4 input file. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">EVAPORATION_IRRIGATION_FRACTION is the fraction of a cropped area that is irrigated but is not covered by a crop. See also the discussion of EVAPORATION_IRRIGATION_FRACTION in the help for the LAND_USE block in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="LAND_USE-Farm-Process-V4-Land-" anchor="EVAPORATION_IRRIGATION_FRACTION" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SURFACEWATER_LOSS_FRACTION_IRRIGATION: indicates the fraction of inefficient losses from irrigation that go to surface water compared to deep percolation.. See also the discussion of SURFACEWATER_LOSS_FRACTION_IRRIGATION in the help for the LAND_USE block in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="LAND_USE-Farm-Process-V4-Land-" anchor="SURFACEWATER_LOSS_FRACTION_IRRIGATION" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
